laboratory_examinations.findings: New atrial fibrillation with a rapid ventricular response; QTc interval 466 msec.
Left atrial and left ventricular dilatation, low-normal left ventricular ejection fraction, mild left ventricular hypertrophy, no clinically significant valvular disease.
Atrial fibrillation with occasional premature ventricular contractions, ventricular rate of 90 beats per minute.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Atrial fibrillation with rapid ventricular response and nonspecific ST-segment changes.
Two episodes of near syncope correlated with sinus pauses of 6 seconds and 7 seconds.
